HEADWORD: Zygapophysis
<hw>Zyg`a*poph"y*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Zygapophyses</plw> <pr>(?)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a yoke + E.
<ets>apophysis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the
articular processes of a vertebra, of which there are usually four, two
anterior and two posterior. See under <er>Vertebra</er>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Zyg`ap*o*phys"i*al</wf> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
